div.p:
It conſiſts of ſharp fixt ſaline Particles;
but has few volatile oily Ones, as appears by
Diſtillation, or Chymical Analyſis.

Its Virtues are the ſame as the former;
but it is not ſo ſtrong: It has the ſame Ge-
nerical Mark alſo as the former.

The Doſe of the Root in Subſtance is to
two Drams; in Decoction to half an Ounce;
for the Elaterium is only given to half a Grain,
or to two.

body.p:
Take candied Eryngo, candied Satyrion, of each
two Drams; Eggs, Fennel, of each one Dram;
Ambergreaſe three Grains; Musk one Grain;
Syrup of Lemons what ſuffices to make an
Electuary.

div.p:
It is, as the former, Epiphylloſpermous;
and therefore is us'd in the ſame Caſes, as it is,
but is ſtronger and more effectual.
